# CODEOWNERS — the coverage/test GATE is human-owned.
#
# These paths define HOW features are gated (what's measured, the thresholds,
# the CI jobs). An autonomous coding agent writes features + tests in the same
# PR that must pass the gate, so if it could edit the gate it could weaken it.
# Assigning these paths to a human means any PR touching them requires a review
# the agent cannot supply.
#
# TEETH: only enforced when branch protection on `main` has
# "Require review from Code Owners" enabled AND the author cannot self-approve.
# See docs/development-lifecycle.md.

